  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the <strong>pizza bottoms</strong> from going soggy!)</p><p>Meanwhile, finely slice the <strong>baby button mushrooms</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Sliced-baby-button-mushrooms-and-chopped-garlic-1685704669511-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Sliced-baby-button-mushrooms-and-chopped-garlic-1685704669511-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Sliced-baby-button-mushrooms-and-chopped-garlic-1685704669511-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Sliced-baby-button-mushrooms-and-chopped-garlic-1685704669511-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Sliced-baby-button-mushrooms-and-chopped-garlic-1685704669511-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sausage meat </strong>(remove the paper if required!), breaking it up into small pieces with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Cook for 3 min or until the sausage meat has browned slightly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640194762277-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640194762277-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640194762277-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640194762277-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1640194762277-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat has browned, add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> and cook for 2 min further until the mushrooms have started to caramelise (no pink meat!)– this is your <strong>sausage & mushroom mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640194769050-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640194769050-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640194769050-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640194769050-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1640194769050-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 5 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [10 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1640194774133-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1640194774133-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1640194774133-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1640194774133-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1640194774133-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1640194782224-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1640194782224-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1640194782224-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1640194782224-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1640194782224-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> from the oven and add the <strong>pizza bases</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> between the pizza bases and spread it evenly all over them with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with the <strong>torn mozzarella</strong> and <strong>sausage & mushroom mixture</strong></p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 13-15 min or until the mozzarella has melted and the pizza bases are crisp</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1640194788618-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1640194788618-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1640194788618-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1640194788618-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1640194788618-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pizzas are cooking, combine the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with the <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>in a small bowl<strong> </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>garlic & herb dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1640194790636-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1640194790636-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1640194790636-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1640194790636-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1640194790636-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sausage & mushroom pizzas</strong> with the<strong> garlic & herb dip</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
